{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/colic-infantile/how-this-topic-was-developed/organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"b6b34c02-df1a-5c7b-968d-706b2b7c6ec3","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 6d6081c5-73d4-4c05-abd5-a7f3000df984 --><h2>Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers</h2><!-- end field 6d6081c5-73d4-4c05-abd5-a7f3000df984 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 2af889c4-20d7-4110-8580-a7f3000c45d5 --><!-- begin field cbdbb6e4-9d68-4857-8e28-a7f3000df984 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field cbdbb6e4-9d68-4857-8e28-a7f3000df984 --><!-- begin field 13f4ccec-f76c-40a2-aac4-a7f3000df984 --><p>The CKS literature searches take into consideration the following concepts, which are discussed at the initial scoping of the topic.</p><ul><li>Feasibility<ul><li>Studies are selected depending on whether the intervention under investigation is available in the NHS and can be practically and safely undertaken in primary care.</li></ul></li><li>Organizational and Financial Impact Analysis</li><li>Studies are selected and evaluated on whether the intervention under investigations may have an impact on local clinical service provision or national impact on cost for the NHS. The principles of clinical budget impact analysis are adhered to, evaluated and recorded by the author. The following factors are considered when making this assessment and analysis.<ul><li>Eligible population</li><li>Current interventions</li><li>Likely uptake of new intervention or recommendation</li><li>Cost of the current or new intervention mix</li><li>Impact on other costs</li><li>Condition-related costs</li><li>In-direct costs and service impacts</li><li>Time dependencies</li></ul></li><li>Cost-effectiveness or cost-benefit analysis studies are identified where available. </li></ul><p>We also evaluate and include evidence from NICE accredited sources which provide economic evaluations of recommendations, such as NICE guidelines. When a recommended action may not be possible because of resource constraints, this is explicitly indicated to healthcare professionals by the wording of the CKS recommendation.</p><!-- end field 13f4ccec-f76c-40a2-aac4-a7f3000df984 --><!-- end item 2af889c4-20d7-4110-8580-a7f3000c45d5 -->","topic":{"id":"e728c26a-005e-5e2a-9f46-f7dfec2cd36d","topicId":"254c369e-40fc-4169-bb92-30394399e7a4","topicName":"Colic - infantile","slug":"colic-infantile","lastRevised":"Last revised in June 2017","chapters":[{"id":"7a1f51d7-41cf-55a8-b71c-4d46909d5b0d","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9d366893-0b5e-5935-a891-e27308683472","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"92f7cd8e-be30-5c7a-9859-062f74d2fd76","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"29f83c05-485a-5dfe-9c41-548aa53dac7e","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"74255d9b-c133-5715-b340-d8bcf73ede99","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"b8fa0a59-acfb-55c8-9dcd-622a14e70f4e","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"85fb7ab5-907c-53bb-9341-53b717308830","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"3f55b4fd-1c0a-517f-8936-e05ef8f1c1f4","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"2684a3a6-6535-5c17-9352-e8dfae930813","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"8fc37b28-2832-51b0-8068-54d4b3ba6bf1","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id":"d9fff9d3-37f5-5235-a336-f9a5c34ad1f5","slug":"qipp-options-for-local-implementation","fullItemName":"QIPP - Options for local implementation"},{"id":"464b9f75-1b8f-55fe-883e-0c2cee1438f9